FBIS4-13083 "drnes074_r_94005" FBIS-NES-94-074 Daily Report 16 Apr 1994 India Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord Rao Defends Signing of GATT Accord BK1704090394 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 1630 GMT 16 Apr 94 BK1704090394 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network English BFN [Text] The prime minister has strongly defended the signing of the GATT treaty by India and urged the people not to be misled by the opposition propaganda. Addressing a public meeting in Port Blair yesterday, he said the country has to be a partner in the global trade treaty for the sake of faster development. Mr. Rao said the small-scale sector will not in any way be affected by India joining the multilateral trade system.
